Message-ID: <GV1P192MB24433EB34771C829D85C6E55FB852@GV1P192MB2443.EURP192.PROD.OUTLOOK.COM>

Hi,

We are estimating predation of sticklebacks on copepods and jellyfish.

In the lab, sticklebacks are offered prey in densities from 2 - 96 ind. per L in separate trials lasting from 5 to 90 minutes.

Time (T) varies as we do not replace ingested prey and target a clearance of max 50 % of the prey.

We have tried fitting non-replacement predator-prey models using the frair package (Pritchard 2017).
We used the function frair_fit with the response type "rogersII" which is a Holling type II response accounting
for non-replacement.

However, the package does not allow for a variable T.

Have anyone encountered this issue and consequently possess code that can handle this,
including the use of Lambert W?

Best regards,
